  <text>
      <front>
         <p>1878? to Harding<note xml:id="ftn2-307" place="foot" n="307">ATL MS-Copy-Micro-0485-1.</note>
         </p>
      </front>
      <body>
         <p rend="end">Friday 10<hi rend="sup ">th</hi>.</p>
         <p>Mr Harding</p>
         <p>My Dear Sir</p>
         <p>You have a little account against me—will you kindly get it made out by (say) Monday next—when weather &amp;c permitting,—I hope to call &amp; pay you.—A few of the Books were for the schools and I shall <hi rend="italic">need </hi>the acct. on my way to Mr. Tylee.—</p>
         <p>I hope you are quite well. I have not seen you for a long time. I have been again laid up (this time, 8–9 days in bed,—with plenty of pain)—</p>
         <p>                                     I am            Yours truly</p>
         <p>                                                     Wm Colenso.</p>
      </body>
